# Warden Architecture — system block diagram (current model)
# Source for "Warden Architecture.svg"  (regenerate: d2 "Warden Architecture.d2" "Warden Architecture.svg")
# Three groupings, left to right: how a rule is DEFINED, how rules COMPOSE + are ADOPTED,
# and how the ENGINE runs them. Bulleted lists inside each box; one level deep; no flow arrows.

direction: right

grid: {
  label: ""
  grid-rows: 1
  grid-gap: 80
  style: { stroke: transparent; fill: transparent }

  define: {
    label: |md
      **DEFINE** — a rule on disk
      - `RULE` / `RULESET` sentinels — greppable
      - **condition**: `where` · `when` · `if`
      - **actions**: `tell` · `edit` · `deny` · `run`
      - `description::` — the meaning (never sent)
    |
    style: { fill: "#e9eeff"; stroke: "#5566aa"; stroke-width: 2 }
  }

  compose: {
    label: |md
      **COMPOSE & ADOPT** — how rules aggregate
      - `include::` → depth-first flatten · umbrellas
      - three homes: catalog · embedded · anchor-local
      - adopt: anchor **traits** + `{NAME} Decisions`
      - `where::` keeps unmatched rules asleep
    |
    style: { fill: "#fff4e6"; stroke: "#c98a3a"; stroke-width: 2 }
  }

  run: {
    label: |md
      **RUN** — the engine
      - resident **daemon** + tiny notifier (~ms / moment)
      - **dispatch**: `where`/`when` indexes → one call
      - **interpret**: `if` + body over `file`·`anchor`·`git`·`event`·`agent`
      - **consumers**: live hooks · `/audit`
      - **oracle**: Sonnet via `claude -p`
    |
    style: { fill: "#e8f7ee"; stroke: "#3a9a5c"; stroke-width: 2 }
  }
}
